.TH "TAKO" "1" "Jun 2026" "Tako CLI" "Tako CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
tako-domains-status - Check DNS routing and TLS readiness for configured or ad-hoc domains


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBtako domains status [domain...] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Check public domain DNS and TLS readiness without redeploying.

.PP
Without arguments, Tako checks the explicit proxy domains configured for the
selected environment. With domain arguments, Tako checks those domains as
ad-hoc domains against the same expected proxy targets.

.PP
The check is flexible: a domain is considered active when HTTPS works, even if
DNS resolves through a CDN or external proxy instead of directly to the VPS.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for status

.PP
\fB-s\fP, \fB--service\fP=""
	Only check configured domains for one service

.PP
\fB--strict\fP[=false]
	Exit non-zero if any checked domain is not active

.PP
\fB--target\fP=[]
	Expected DNS target; repeat for custom edge/CNAME targets (defaults to proxy server hosts)

.PP
\fB--wait\fP=0s
	Wait up to this duration for DNS/TLS to become active (for example 2m); 0 checks once


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is ./tako.yaml or ./tako.json)

.PP
\fB-e\fP, \fB--env\fP=""
	environment to deploy (default: production or only environment)

.PP
\fB--events\fP=""
	stream progress events to stdout: ndjson (human output moves to stderr)

.PP
\fB--host-key-mode\fP=""
	SSH host key verification mode: tofu, strict, ask (default: tofu)

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	output format: text or json (json reserves stdout for the final result document)

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	verbose output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBtako-domains(1)\fP
